      <head>Musikalienhandlung Rosé</head>
      <div>
        <p>Sheet music retail store located at Vienna I, Kärntnerring 11, owned by Alexander Rosé,
          the elder brother of <ref cRef="entity-000727">Arnold Rosé</ref>. The firm's full name was
          "Kunst- und Musikalienhandlung und Musikalien-Leihanstalt" ("Art and Sheet Music Retailer
          and Music Loan Library"). The firm also operated a concert agency.</p>

        <p>After Alexander Rosé's death, Artur Hainauer became the proprietor of the firm in 1906 or
          1907. In his diary for December 19, 1906, Schenker refers to it as "Musikalienhandlung
          Rosé (Hainauer)."</p>
      </div>

